<!--
# Utility AI - Score-Based Selection

`<HighestScore>` is a selector: each child carries a fixed `{Score}` alongside
its action. The selector scores every child, then runs only the highest-scoring
one and returns its outcome. Here the 0.6 child wins over the 0.4 child.

    beet --main=examples/action/utility_ai.bsx
-->
<HighestScore {RunOnLoad}>
	<Log::Message("this child does not run") {Score(0.4)}/>
	<Log::Message("this child runs") {Score(0.6)}/>
</HighestScore>
